description:
`validateStageCompletion()` in task-dispatcher.mjs bails out with `ok: true` immediately for non-code tasks (`!isCodeTask`). This means coach, researcher, and health agents can complete a task with empty `handoff_notes` and it advances to done with no human-readable summary of what was produced.

Fix: restructure `validateStageCompletion()` so the `handoff_notes` check for `in_progress` stage runs for ALL tasks, not just code tasks:

```js
if (stage === 'in_progress') {
  const handoff = String(task.handoff_notes || '').trim();
  if (!handoff) {
    return { ok: false, reason: `${task.task_id} is missing handoff_notes.`, blockedBy: ['agent:missing-handoff'] };
  }
}
// Only then check isCodeTask for git evidence
if (!isCodeTask) return { ok: true, reason: null, blockedBy: [] };
```

This keeps git evidence checks scoped to code tasks while ensuring all agents must leave a handoff note.
